    "# Advanced Features and Operations of FrequencySeries\n",
    "\n",
    "[![Open In Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg)](https://colab.research.google.com/github/tatsuki-washimi/gwexpy/blob/main/docs/web/en/user_guide/tutorials/intro_frequencyseries.ipynb)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook introduces the new methods and features of the `FrequencySeries` class extended in `gwexpy`.\n",
    "We will focus on handling complex spectra, calculus operations, filtering (smoothing), and integration with other libraries."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,

    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "from gwexpy.frequencyseries import FrequencySeries\n",
    "from gwexpy.plot import Plot\n",
    "from gwexpy.timeseries import TimeSeries\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.rcParams[\"figure.figsize\"] = (10, 6)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Data Preparation\n",
    "\n",
    "First, we create a `FrequencySeries` from a `TimeSeries` using FFT.\n",
    "Here, we generate a test signal with specific frequency components."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-02-26T12:17:49.381561Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-02-26T12:17:49.381197Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-02-26T12:18:01.107354Z",

    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "TimeSeries([-0.30926935,  0.07921011, -0.38691015, ...,\n",
      "             1.5878545 ,  1.02586626,  1.05521698],\n",
      "           unit: um,\n",
      "           t0: 0.0 s,\n",
      "           dt: 0.0009765625 s,\n",
      "           name: Test Signal,\n",
      "           channel: None)\n",
      "Type: <class 'gwexpy.frequencyseries.frequencyseries.FrequencySeries'>\n",
      "Length: 3073\n",
      "df: 0.16666666666666666 Hz\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Plot size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fs = 1024\n",
    "t = np.arange(0, 4, 1 / fs)\n",
    "exp = np.exp(-t / 1.5)\n",
    "exp[: int(exp.size / 4)] = 0\n",
    "data = (\n",
    "    np.sin(2 * np.pi * 10.1 * t)\n",
    "    + 5 * exp * np.sin(2 * np.pi * 100.1 * t)\n",
    "    + np.random.normal(scale=0.3, size=len(t))\n",
    ")\n",
    "ts = TimeSeries(data, dt=1 / fs, unit=\"um\", name=\"Test Signal\")\n",
    "print(ts)\n",
    "ts.plot(title=ts.name)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Perform FFT to obtain FrequencySeries (using transient mode with padding)\n",
    "spec = ts.fft(mode=\"transient\", pad_left=1.0, pad_right=1.0, nfft_mode=\"next_fast_len\")\n",
    "print(f\"Type: {type(spec)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Length: {len(spec)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"df: {spec.df}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Visualization and Conversion of Complex Spectra\n",
    "\n",
    "### Phase and Amplitude\n",
    "Using the `phase()`, `degree()`, and `to_db()` methods, you can convert complex spectra into intuitive units."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-02-26T12:18:01.110622Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-02-26T12:18:01.110495Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-02-26T12:18:01.473019Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-02-26T12:18:01.471528Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Plot size 900x1000 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Convert amplitude to dB (ref=1.0, 20*log10)\n",
    "spec_db = spec.to_db()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get phase (in degrees, unwrap=True for continuity)\n",
    "spec_phase = spec.degree(unwrap=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "plot = Plot(spec_db, spec_phase, separate=True, sharex=True, xscale=\"log\")\n",
    "ax = plot.axes\n",
    "ax[0].set_ylabel(\"Magnitude [dB (m)]\")\n",
    "ax[0].grid(True, which=\"both\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[1].set_ylabel(\"Phase [deg]\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_xlabel(\"Frequency [Hz]\")\n",
    "ax[1].grid(True, which=\"both\")\n",
    "plot.figure.suptitle(\"Complex Spectrum Analysis\")\n",
    "plot.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Calculus in Frequency Domain\n",
    "\n",
    "The `differentiate()` and `integrate()` methods allow you to perform differentiation and integration in the frequency domain.\n",
    "You can specify the order using the `order` argument (default is 1).\n",
    "This feature makes it easy to convert between displacement, velocity, and acceleration (multiplication/division by $(2 \\pi i f)^n$)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-02-26T12:18:01.475259Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-02-26T12:18:01.475129Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-02-26T12:18:01.739706Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-02-26T12:18:01.738312Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Plot size 1000x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Differentiate from displacement (m) to velocity (m/s) (order=1)\n",
    "vel_spec = spec.differentiate()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Differentiate from displacement (m) to acceleration (m/s^2) (order=2)\n",
    "accel_spec = spec.differentiate(order=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Integration is also possible: acceleration -> velocity\n",
    "vel_from_accel = accel_spec.integrate()\n",
    "\n",
    "plot = Plot(\n",
    "    spec.abs(), vel_spec.abs(), accel_spec.abs(), xscale=\"log\", yscale=\"log\", alpha=0.8\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax = plot.gca()\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[0].set_label(\"Displacement [m]\")\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[1].set_label(\"Velocity [m/s]\")\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[2].set_label(\"Acceleration [m/s^2]\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.grid(True, which=\"both\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Calculus in Frequency Domain\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Magnitude\")\n",
    "plot.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Spectrum Smoothing and Peak Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "### Smoothing\n",
    "The `smooth()` method enables smoothing of the spectrum using moving averages and other techniques."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-02-26T12:18:01.742145Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-02-26T12:18:01.742003Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-02-26T12:18:02.046706Z",

     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Plot size 1000x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Smooth in amplitude domain with 11 samples\n",
    "spec_smooth = spec.smooth(width=11)\n",
    "\n",
    "plot = Plot(spec.abs(), spec_smooth.abs(), xscale=\"log\", yscale=\"log\")\n",
    "ax = plot.gca()\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[0].set_label(\"Original\")\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[0].set_alpha(0.6)\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[1].set_label(\"Smoothed (width=11)\")\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[1].set_color(\"red\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.grid(True, which=\"both\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Spectrum Smoothing\")\n",
    "plot.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Peak Detection\n",
    "The `find_peaks()` method wraps `scipy.signal.find_peaks`, making it easy to extract peaks above a specific threshold."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-02-26T12:18:02.048237Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-02-26T12:18:02.048107Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-02-26T12:18:02.274838Z",

     "data": {
      "image/png": "",

       "<Plot size 1000x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Find peaks with amplitude >= 0.2\n",
    "peaks, props = spec.find_peaks(threshold=0.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "plot = Plot(spec.abs())\n",
    "ax = plot.gca()\n",
    "ax.plot(\n",
    "    peaks.abs(), color=\"red\", marker=\".\", ms=15, lw=0, zorder=3, label=\"Detected Peaks\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(1, 150)\n",
    "ax.set_xscale(\"log\")\n",
    "ax.set_yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Peak Detection\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plot.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Advanced Analysis Features\n",
    "\n",
    "### Group Delay\n",
    "The `group_delay()` method calculates the group delay (delay of the signal envelope) from the frequency derivative of the phase."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-02-26T12:18:02.278082Z",

    "gd = spec.group_delay()\n",
    "\n",
    "plot = Plot(gd)\n",
    "ax = plot.gca()\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Group Delay [s]\")\n",

    "plot.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Inverse FFT (ifft)\n",
    "The `ifft()` method returns a `TimeSeries`. Even for results from FFT with `mode=\"transient\"`, it can inherit the information and control restoration to the original length (trim=True)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-02-26T12:18:02.597635Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-02-26T12:18:02.597487Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-02-26T12:18:44.760283Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-02-26T12:18:44.759347Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Plot size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Plot size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Convert back to TimeSeries with inverse FFT\n",
    "# mode=\"auto\" reads the transient information from the input FrequencySeries and processes it appropriately\n",
    "inv_ts = spec.ifft(mode=\"auto\")\n",
    "red_ts = inv_ts - ts\n",
    "\n",
    "plot = Plot(ts, inv_ts, red_ts)\n",
    "ax = plot.gca()\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[0].set_label(\"Original\")\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[1].set_label(\"IFFT Result\")\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[2].set_label(\"Residual\")\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[1].set_linestyle(\"--\")\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[1].set_alpha(0.8)\n",
    "ax.get_lines()[2].set_color(\"black\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Time Domain Round-trip (FFT -> IFFT)\")\n",
    "plot.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "red_ts.plot(title=\"Residual Time Series after IFFT\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

    "# Convert to control.FRD (can be used for control system analysis)\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    from control import FRD\n",
    "\n",
    "    _ = FRD\n",
    "    frd_obj = spec.to_control_frd()\n",
    "    print(\"Successfully converted to control.FRD\")\n",
    "    display(frd_obj)\n",
    "except ImportError:\n",
    "    print(\"python-control library not installed\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

    "## 7. Integration with Python Control Library\n",
    "\n",
    "Interconversion with the **Frequency Response Data (FRD)** object from the `control` library, which is standard in the field of control engineering, is possible.\n",
    "This allows transfer functions measured with GWExPy to be directly used for control system design and analysis."

    "try:\n",
    "    import control\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Convert FrequencySeries -> control.FRD\n",
    "    # Specifying frequency_unit=\"Hz\" appropriately converts to rad/s internally\n",
    "    frd_sys = spec.to_control_frd(frequency_unit=\"Hz\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(\"\\n--- Converted to Control FRD ---\")\n",
    "    print(str(frd_sys)[:1000] + \"\\n... (truncated) ...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Plot Bode diagram (control library functionality)\n",
    "    control.bode(frd_sys)  # (executable if plotting environment is available)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Restore control.FRD -> FrequencySeries\n",
    "    fs_restored = FrequencySeries.from_control_frd(frd_sys, frequency_unit=\"Hz\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(\"\\n--- Restored FrequencySeries ---\")\n",
    "    print(fs_restored)\n",
    "\n",
    "except ImportError:\n",
    "    print(\"Python Control Systems Library is not installed.\")"

    "## 8. Quadrature Sum\n",
    "\n",
    "This feature calculates the sum of orthogonal components."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-02-26T12:18:45.437451Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-02-26T12:18:45.437167Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-02-26T12:18:45.895592Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-02-26T12:18:45.894762Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [

     "data": {
      "image/png": "",

       "<Plot size 1000x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]

     "metadata": {},

     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Noise A: 1.0, Noise B: 2.0\n",
      "Total (Sqrt Sum): 2.23606797749979\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Plot size 1000x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Generate noisy data\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "f = spec.frequencies.value\n",
    "noise = np.abs(np.random.randn(f.size))\n",
    "peak = 10.0 * np.exp(-((f - 200) ** 2) / 50.0)\n",
    "data = noise + peak\n",
    "\n",
    "raw = FrequencySeries(data, frequencies=f, unit=\"V\", name=\"Raw Data\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Smooth\n",
    "smoothed = raw.smooth(width=10, method=\"amplitude\")\n",
    "smoothed.name = \"Smoothed\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert to dB\n",
    "raw_db = raw.to_db()\n",
    "smoothed_db = smoothed.to_db()\n",
    "raw_db.name = \"Raw (dB)\"\n",
    "smoothed_db.name = \"Smoothed (dB)\"\n",
    "\n",
    "plot = raw_db.plot(label=\"Raw\", title=\"Smoothing & dB\")\n",
    "ax = plot.gca()\n",
    "ax.plot(smoothed_db, label=\"Smoothed\", linewidth=2)\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plot.show()\n",
    "plt.close()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Quadrature Sum (Noise Budget example)\n",
    "noise_a = FrequencySeries(np.ones_like(f), frequencies=f, unit=\"V\", name=\"Noise A\")\n",
    "noise_b = FrequencySeries(np.ones_like(f) * 2, frequencies=f, unit=\"V\", name=\"Noise B\")\n",
    "\n",
    "total = noise_a.quadrature_sum(noise_b)\n",
    "print(f\"Noise A: {noise_a.value[0]}, Noise B: {noise_b.value[0]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total (Sqrt Sum): {total.value[0]}\")\n",
    "Plot(total, noise_a, noise_b, alpha=0.8)\n",
    "plt.legend([\"Total\", \"Noise A\", \"Noise B\"])\n",
    "plt.xscale(\"log\")\n",
    "plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
